---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets'
import BuyButtons from '@components/pages/Home/components/BuyButtons.astro'
import businessManImage from '@images/mktg/business-man-1.png'
import { Construction } from '@lucide/astro'
---

<section id="problem-statement" class="bg-base-100 bg-circuit">
  <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
    <!-- Main Headline -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="text-accent text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-bold font-heading mb-6">
        <Construction class="inline-block h-9 w-9 ml-2" />
      </p>
      <h1
        class="text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-heading font-bold text-base-content mb-8 leading-tight"
      >
        Building <span class="text-primary">modern</span>, <span
          class="text-primary">reliable</span
        >, and <span class="text-primary">extensible</span> web applications is still
        surprisingly
        <span
          class="text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-primary to-secondary bg-clip-text"
          >hard</span
        >!
      </h1>
      <p class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl text-base-content/80 font-heading">
        But it doesn't have to be...
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Problem Statement -->
    <div
      class="max-w-6xl justify-self-center bg-base-100/80 rounded-2xl p-8 lg:p-12 shadow border border-base-300/50 mb-12"
    >
      <p
        class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-base-content/90 font-sans leading-relaxed mb-8"
      >
        If you've landed here, you've probably been down the rabbit hole,
        reading articles, watching videos, and following tutorials, hoping to
        finally <strong>get good at Node.js</strong>.
      </p>

      <p
        class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-base-content/90 font-sans leading-relaxed mb-8"
      >
        Maybe you've used Node.js before, but&hellip;
      </p>

      <!-- Pain Points List -->
      <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-base-content/80">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent rounded-full mt-3 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-lg font-sans"
            >You can't quite explain how the <strong>event loop</strong> really works.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-base-content/80">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent rounded-full mt-3 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-lg font-sans"
            ><strong>Callbacks</strong>, <strong>promises</strong>, and <strong
              >async</strong
            > flows still trip you up occasionally.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-base-content/80">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent rounded-full mt-3 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-lg font-sans"
            >Writing <strong>concurrent code</strong> feels messy and unpredictable.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-base-content/80">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent rounded-full mt-3 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-lg font-sans"
            >As your project grows, so does the chaos, and you're unsure how to
            keep things <strong>organized</strong>, <strong>scalable</strong>,
            and <strong>maintainable</strong></span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-base-content/80">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent rounded-full mt-3 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-lg font-sans"
            ><strong>Testing</strong>? You avoid it, because it just feels too
            hard to get right.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4 text-base-content/80">
          <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent rounded-full mt-3 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-lg font-sans"
            >You see the value in <strong>microservices</strong>, but managing
            instances, distributing load, and handling messaging patterns still
            feels overwhelming.</span
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Solution -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-base-content font-heading mb-6"
      >
        We get it. We've been there too!
      </h2>
      <p class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl text-base-content/80 font-heading">
        That's exactly why we wrote Node.js Design Patterns.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Value Proposition with Image -->
    <div
      class="bg-base-100/80 rounded-2xl p-8 lg:p-12 shadow border border-primary/30 mb-12"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 lg:gap-12 items-center">
        <!-- Text Content -->
        <div class="flex-1 space-y-6">
          <p
            class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-base-content leading-relaxed font-sans"
          >
            This book exists to guide you through all the fundamentals with
            clarity and purpose, and it doesn't stop there.
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-base-content leading-relaxed font-sans"
          >
            You'll walk through carefully crafted code examples, learn how to
            master asynchronous flows, write clean and testable code, and apply
            battle-tested design and architectural patterns that scale.
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-base-content leading-relaxed font-sans"
          >
            From modular design and dependency injection to scalability,
            messaging, and integration patterns, this is the bread and butter of
            senior developers who build complex, distributed systems with
            confidence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Image -->
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex justify-center w-full lg:w-80 xl:w-96">
          <Picture
            src={businessManImage}
            alt="Professional reading Node.js Design Patterns book"
            formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
            widths={[320, 480, 640, 800]}
            sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 50vw, 400px"
            pictureAttributes={{
              class: 'max-w-[400px] lg:max-w-[800px]',
            }}
            class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Call to Action -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-base-content font-heading mb-6"
      >
        Stop stitching together half-solutions.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl text-base-content/80 font-heading">
        Start learning Node.js the way it was meant to be learned.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <BuyButtons />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
